00:45:21.860 --> 00:45:26.060
Jefferson, and by the way, this
building is named after him,

00:45:26.060 --> 00:45:29.730
he accumulated nearly all
treatises on the subject

00:45:29.730 --> 00:45:34.140
of natural law Grotius, Pufendorf,
Wolff and, of course, not one

00:45:34.140 --> 00:45:37.600
but two different editions
of Vattel's Law of Nations.

00:45:37.600 --> 00:45:40.470
Jefferson's copy of Vattel's
later edition which he loan

00:45:40.470 --> 00:45:42.190
to representative from
North Carolina

00:45:42.190 --> 00:45:45.420
and to another representative
from Rhode Island reveals

00:45:45.420 --> 00:45:48.880
that the cross-- that he cross
reference Vattel on the Law

00:45:48.880 --> 00:45:50.480
of Nations with the work

00:45:50.480 --> 00:45:53.140
of the German juror
George Fredrickson Martins

00:45:53.140 --> 00:45:54.440
[assumed spelling].

00:45:54.440 --> 00:45:56.690
In referencing Vattel's
work to that of Bodin,

00:45:56.690 --> 00:46:00.770 position:56%
the 16th century political theorist,
Jefferson positioned the theory

00:46:00.770 --> 00:46:04.280
of domestic sovereignty within
the larger context of relations

00:46:04.280 --> 00:46:06.330
between independent states.

00:46:06.330 --> 00:46:11.020
Sovereignty as independence, the
main justification for waging a war

00:46:11.020 --> 00:46:15.280
against British oppression was
located into the larger context

00:46:15.280 --> 00:46:19.630
of relations between states and the
law of nature as applied to them.

00:46:19.630 --> 00:46:23.420
In bringing my story to an end,

00:46:23.420 --> 00:46:25.810
allow me to draw three
main conclusions.

00:46:25.810 --> 00:46:29.250
The first one should be
quite obvious by now, mainly,

00:46:29.250 --> 00:46:33.290
that far from being marginal and
irrelevant, marginal at best,

00:46:33.290 --> 00:46:38.740
irrelevant at worst, Vattel was
in fact at the heart of debate

00:46:38.740 --> 00:46:42.310
in the early American republic over
the core ideals of the revolution

00:46:42.310 --> 00:46:45.390
that produced a political
conditions for life, liberty

00:46:45.390 --> 00:46:47.670
and the pursuit of happiness.

00:46:47.670 --> 00:46:50.790
While many of us are
continually reminded of the impact

00:46:50.790 --> 00:46:53.930
of John Locke's political
theory exercise on the birth

00:46:53.930 --> 00:46:56.610
of this nation, and
I'm not denying that,

00:46:56.610 --> 00:47:00.660
the authority of Vattel was
significantly I think far more

00:47:00.660 --> 00:47:03.720
reaching and far more lasting.

00:47:03.720 --> 00:47:07.210
Vattel over lock, conclusion one.

00:47:07.210 --> 00:47:12.180
Second conclusion, it isn't a
way a corollary of the first,

00:47:12.180 --> 00:47:16.570
while we consistently regard
independence as the hard one price

00:47:16.570 --> 00:47:19.050
of the revolutionaries
and I'm not denying that.

00:47:19.050 --> 00:47:22.510
I think in fact it
was interdependence

00:47:22.510 --> 00:47:25.170
that was central to their ideology.

00:47:25.170 --> 00:47:28.390
They had to become independent
in the first place in order

00:47:28.390 --> 00:47:32.420
to realize their independence
in a world of states.

00:47:32.420 --> 00:47:36.930
They did so by making use of
available language of the Law

00:47:36.930 --> 00:47:41.510
of Nations, a language which
Vattel so conveniently yet,

00:47:41.510 --> 00:47:45.590
conclusion number two, so
unintentionally provided to them.

00:47:45.590 --> 00:47:50.400
In short the boundary between home
and abroad was merely imaginary.

00:47:50.400 --> 00:47:54.370
Americas have always been
part of a much larger world.

00:47:54.370 --> 00:47:58.040
The third conclusion, and this
is the final conclusion I want

00:47:58.040 --> 00:48:01.720
to leave you with, how we should
transform our understanding

00:48:01.720 --> 00:48:03.380
of the American revolution.

00:48:03.380 --> 00:48:06.490
Unlike the French revolution,
which has always been regarded

00:48:06.490 --> 00:48:09.080 position:56%
as truly international in its reach,

00:48:09.080 --> 00:48:12.030
the American Revolution
has generally

00:48:12.030 --> 00:48:16.250
and there has been recent changes
in scholarship on this point,

00:48:16.250 --> 00:48:18.740
that American revolution has
generally been seen as the marking

00:48:18.740 --> 00:48:20.540
of the birth of a new nation.

00:48:20.540 --> 00:48:22.350
And I'm not denying that story,

00:48:22.350 --> 00:48:27.780
but the story I have told you
today should unsettle this very

00:48:27.780 --> 00:48:29.240
common belief.

00:48:29.240 --> 00:48:32.620
It was not simply a domestic
revolution for independence,

00:48:32.620 --> 00:48:35.410
it was primarily the
beginning of the modern state.

00:48:35.410 --> 00:48:41.870
Writing in 1963, the political
thinker, very prominent,

00:48:41.870 --> 00:48:47.350
Hannah Arendt writes and I quote,
"The sad truth of the matter is

00:48:47.350 --> 00:48:49.010
that the French Revolution,

00:48:49.010 --> 00:48:53.190
which ended in disaster
has made world history,

00:48:53.190 --> 00:48:55.110
while the American Revolution,

00:48:55.110 --> 00:48:59.280
so triumphantly successful
has remained an event

00:48:59.280 --> 00:49:02.430
of little more than
local importance."

00:49:02.430 --> 00:49:07.190
The American Revolution as
I've to show was an event

00:49:07.190 --> 00:49:13.080 position:56%
of a truly global significance whose
effects can be felt with us today.

00:49:13.080 --> 00:49:19.560
Ironically none of these effects
were in any way intended by Vattel

00:49:19.560 --> 00:49:24.960
and yet he would gratefully take
credit for them as he should.

00:49:24.960 --> 00:49:26.760
Thanks for the attention.

00:49:26.760 --> 00:49:39.440
