00:50:21.070 --> 00:50:31.090
however in your lecture,
and think in this way,

00:50:31.090 --> 00:50:38.280
Vattel talks about
nations in a context

00:50:38.280 --> 00:50:45.910
of nature as I understand it.

00:50:45.910 --> 00:50:53.720 position:56%
And he talks about state, he doesn't
talk about nations [inaudible].

00:50:53.720 --> 00:51:00.810
And particularly my question is
how we get from these categories

00:51:00.810 --> 00:51:06.910
of nations and states and impart
the distinction that we can gather

00:51:06.910 --> 00:51:12.220
in 20th, we nation states and
[inaudible] this distinction

00:51:12.220 --> 00:51:17.010
that is embedded in the
arguments of Vattel [inaudible]

00:51:17.010 --> 00:51:21.650
or is it something
that comes a little--

00:51:21.650 --> 00:51:24.530
&gt;&gt; Theo Christov: Great question.

00:51:24.530 --> 00:51:28.990
That's really the heart
of what I'm trying to do,

00:51:28.990 --> 00:51:33.980
how we transition from
empire to states.

00:51:33.980 --> 00:51:37.510
Let me just say what
Vattel is not doing.

00:51:37.510 --> 00:51:40.500
Vattel is not endorsing
any imperial ways

00:51:40.500 --> 00:51:44.690
of perpetuating the European
experience of empires

00:51:44.690 --> 00:51:46.840
in the 18th century,
he speaks of nations.

00:51:46.840 --> 00:51:52.030
And actually he speaks of
patriarch in the French edition.

00:51:52.030 --> 00:51:57.420
So he-- he's very much
thinking in terms of homelands.

00:51:57.420 --> 00:52:00.360
He's not thinking in terms
of the nation and state

00:52:00.360 --> 00:52:02.210
as we would understand it today.

00:52:02.210 --> 00:52:06.260
Now, that is not to say that the
revolutionaries were not making use

00:52:06.260 --> 00:52:07.560
to their own ends, and part

00:52:07.560 --> 00:52:11.510
of my argument is there have
been unintended consequences

00:52:11.510 --> 00:52:18.530
of using Vattel for purposes of
claiming independence in order

00:52:18.530 --> 00:52:20.970
to claim interdependence
among other states.

00:52:20.970 --> 00:52:24.390
So in other words what
I'm trying to say is

00:52:24.390 --> 00:52:29.640
that Vattel's argument is
being used to make claims

00:52:29.640 --> 00:52:32.250
for external sovereignty.

00:52:32.250 --> 00:52:36.810
But in order to make a claim
for external sovereignty,

00:52:36.810 --> 00:52:40.360
you have to have a claim
to domestic sovereignty.

00:52:40.360 --> 00:52:42.800
And the thing we've lost track of
the second part of the equation,

00:52:42.800 --> 00:52:48.380
we focus so much on domestic
independence and sovereignty,

00:52:48.380 --> 00:52:51.990
we've lost track of the
external sovereignty.

00:52:51.990 --> 00:53:00.760 position:56%
I think what Vattel is doing is he's
giving us the legitimacy criteria

00:53:00.760 --> 00:53:04.240
according to which
we can make a claim

00:53:04.240 --> 00:53:10.290
for how a state can become an
equal member of the international

00:53:10.290 --> 00:53:14.180
and I don't like to use
the word society of states,

00:53:14.180 --> 00:53:22.020
but essentially what he is doing
is enumerating the conditions

00:53:22.020 --> 00:53:24.000
on which we can claim independence.

00:53:24.000 --> 00:53:35.020
And he's making that
argument on various point,

00:53:35.020 --> 00:53:44.350
I'm not going to go too much into
it, but he's making distinction

00:53:44.350 --> 00:53:46.270
between free persons
and free states,

00:53:46.270 --> 00:53:56.180
that there is an analogy
between the two.

00:53:56.180 --> 00:54:02.030
That analogy breaks down
because free persons come

00:54:02.030 --> 00:54:06.510
and institute society, but free
states don't necessarily come

00:54:06.510 --> 00:54:07.900
and institute a global society.

00:54:07.900 --> 00:54:13.000
But I think what is critical is
that Vattel speaks of independence

00:54:13.000 --> 00:54:14.560
as a condition for interdependence.

00:54:14.560 --> 00:54:17.010
And I think that part
of the argument is taken

00:54:17.010 --> 00:54:19.300
up by the early Americans.

00:54:19.300 --> 00:54:25.360
So I think your point is well taken
that we have to be careful to speak

00:54:25.360 --> 00:54:27.800 position:56%
of nation states in the 20th century

00:54:27.800 --> 00:54:31.380
and perhaps even how those
nation states are being unsettled

00:54:31.380 --> 00:54:32.680
by non state actors.

00:54:32.680 --> 00:54:35.790
But I do think Vattel's approach
of taking interdependence

00:54:35.790 --> 00:54:43.180
as a consequent-- consequence
of independence is critical

00:54:43.180 --> 00:54:45.060
that we have to start
with independence

00:54:45.060 --> 00:54:48.010 position:56%
and then move on to interdependence.

00:54:48.010 --> 00:54:49.340
I hope that answers
part of the question.

00:54:49.340 --> 00:54:50.640
Yes?

00:54:50.640 --> 00:54:51.940
&gt;&gt; How, you know, how does this
