00:56:34.740 --> 00:56:36.690
because one simple reason,
in addition to the fact

00:56:36.690 --> 00:56:40.580
that they develop commercial
relations, British love liberty

00:56:40.580 --> 00:56:42.830
in a way that no other nation does.

00:56:42.830 --> 00:56:44.740
And I think it's very
critical for him

00:56:44.740 --> 00:56:47.620
that he doesn't endorse the French,
he doesn't endorse even the Swiss,

00:56:47.620 --> 00:56:50.220
he himself is a Swiss,
he's from Neuchatel.

00:56:50.220 --> 00:56:52.350
And by the way, he's a
contemporary of Rosso,

00:56:52.350 --> 00:56:56.420 position:56%
but yet he's very much engaging with
the British because they provide

00:56:56.420 --> 00:56:58.070
that blueprint for liberty.

00:56:58.070 --> 00:57:01.680
So I do think that he's very
much embraced on the island,

00:57:01.680 --> 00:57:04.700
but within continental Europe,
he's much more questionable.

00:57:04.700 --> 00:57:07.320
And I think this also a very
interesting point to make,

00:57:07.320 --> 00:57:13.450
how he's being used and how
his theory has been transformed

00:57:13.450 --> 00:57:15.160
in the American context.

00:57:15.160 --> 00:57:19.010 position:56%
He was not writing for the Americans
and yet in the hands, precisely,

00:57:19.010 --> 00:57:24.290
of the editor Charles Dumas, he
was able to be very much used here.

00:57:24.290 --> 00:57:26.110
And the first part
of the question was

00:57:26.110 --> 00:57:28.450
that on any relation with Grotius?

00:57:28.450 --> 00:57:32.110
So Grotius was the early
17th century Dutch jurist

00:57:32.110 --> 00:57:36.420
and Vattel comes about a
130, a 140 years later.

00:57:36.420 --> 00:57:40.970 position:56%
It's a very interesting question
because Grotius in many ways is seen

00:57:40.970 --> 00:57:43.670
as much more rigid on the
question of intervention.

00:57:43.670 --> 00:57:46.340
Vattel on the other hand is--

00:57:46.340 --> 00:57:48.520
although that's even
somewhat questionable,

00:57:48.520 --> 00:57:52.960
but I think he's much more reserved
on the question, can intervention

00:57:52.960 --> 00:57:56.840
within international
relations is that permissible.

00:57:56.840 --> 00:58:01.750
I think in general Vattel would say
no at least in relation to Grotius.

00:58:01.750 --> 00:58:03.610
What connects both
Grotius and Vattel

00:58:03.610 --> 00:58:08.270
and by the way there's also a third
name Pufendorf because in 1785,

00:58:08.270 --> 00:58:11.930 position:56%
Immanuel Kant writes of all three of
them, Grotius, Pufendorf and Vattel

00:58:11.930 --> 00:58:13.930
as sorry comforters, why?

00:58:13.930 --> 00:58:15.590
Simply because they were not--

00:58:15.590 --> 00:58:19.480
they were simply very fanciful
with their legal theories

00:58:19.480 --> 00:58:21.130
because you cannot
put them in practice.

00:58:21.130 --> 00:58:22.830
I think it's a struggle
we have today.

00:58:22.830 --> 00:58:26.540
Can international law be
imposed or is simple chimerical?

00:58:26.540 --> 00:58:29.000
According to Immanuel Kant,
they were simply chimerical.

00:58:29.000 --> 00:58:33.940 position:56%
So Grotius, Vattel and Pufendorf was
the three he calls sorry comforters,

00:58:33.940 --> 00:58:37.450
because they're just comforting us,
but actually we should feel sorry

00:58:37.450 --> 00:58:39.630
for that because they're not
really providing anything.

00:58:39.630 --> 00:58:43.350
But Grotius is very much
I think coming out of--

00:58:43.350 --> 00:58:46.050
and I have actually a reason
to say this, he's really coming

00:58:46.050 --> 00:58:50.860
out of use especially in 19th
century because citations,

00:58:50.860 --> 00:58:55.500
Vattel in the 19th century in
legal-- in the Supreme Court cases,

00:58:55.500 --> 00:58:58.560
in legal proceedings
far exceed those

00:58:58.560 --> 00:59:01.190
of Grotius and Pufendorf combined.

00:59:01.190 --> 00:59:03.520
So I think the legacy of
Grotius is still there,

00:59:03.520 --> 00:59:06.130
but I think question
is practical use.

00:59:06.130 --> 00:59:09.190
This was a practical guidebook,
Americans really needed

00:59:09.190 --> 00:59:11.390
