01:01:09.770 --> 01:01:13.320
I think there's issues with
that because it's not really

01:01:13.320 --> 01:01:14.750
until the question

01:01:14.750 --> 01:01:20.600
of how independence
provides the first condition

01:01:20.600 --> 01:01:22.310
for external recognition.

01:01:22.310 --> 01:01:25.260
And in many ways that's what
I'm trying to argue in my point

01:01:25.260 --> 01:01:28.350
that you cannot establish
external recognition,

01:01:28.350 --> 01:01:31.100
meaning outside recognizing you

01:01:31.100 --> 01:01:36.860 position:56%
as a state before you claim
domestic autonomy of a certain kind.

01:01:36.860 --> 01:01:38.390
Now, there's very-- various ways

01:01:38.390 --> 01:01:41.280 position:56%
in which one can establish political
autonomy and I think someone

01:01:41.280 --> 01:01:42.980
like Vattel is more reserved

01:01:42.980 --> 01:01:45.640
about how he should structure
our political system.

01:01:45.640 --> 01:01:47.050
He's open to various kinds

01:01:47.050 --> 01:01:49.550
of political systems
and political regimes.

01:01:49.550 --> 01:01:54.310 position:56%
What is critical is to establish the
conditions for domestic sovereignty,

01:01:54.310 --> 01:01:58.390
then and only then external
recondition can be demanded.

01:01:58.390 --> 01:02:01.520
And that's exactly what I think
people like David Armitage

01:02:01.520 --> 01:02:03.610
for instance have insisted
the declaration

01:02:03.610 --> 01:02:07.960
of independence is a legal document
in relation to international law.

01:02:07.960 --> 01:02:13.530 position:56%
How the birth of what we can call
today international law began by way

01:02:13.530 --> 01:02:17.230
of moving from independence
to interdependence.

01:02:17.230 --> 01:02:21.080
In other words, you're not simply
on autonomous entity existing

01:02:21.080 --> 01:02:24.240
on your own, but you're in
relation in a sort of web

01:02:24.240 --> 01:02:26.390
of relations with other states.

01:02:26.390 --> 01:02:29.800
And I think the birth of the
United States provides that kind

01:02:29.800 --> 01:02:33.510
of pivotal moment because
in many ways, let's face it,

01:02:33.510 --> 01:02:37.170
America was a fortunate
circumstance,

01:02:37.170 --> 01:02:40.960
because nature favored
them in many ways.

01:02:40.960 --> 01:02:45.400
And I think that fortunate
circumstance provided the impetus

01:02:45.400 --> 01:02:49.000
for how in the 19th and
especially in the second half

01:02:49.000 --> 01:02:53.810 position:56%
of the 20th century the number of
states would quadruple from about 50

01:02:53.810 --> 01:02:55.110
around the time that the founding

01:02:55.110 --> 01:02:58.150
into United Nations
to almost 200 today.

01:02:58.150 --> 01:03:02.440 position:56%
And I think Vattel is providing that
kind of prescriptive model moving

01:03:02.440 --> 01:03:05.630
from independence to
interdependence.

01:03:05.630 --> 01:03:06.970
He's also very explicit

01:03:06.970 --> 01:03:10.670
that independence is can sometimes
be very violent and very bloody.

01:03:10.670 --> 01:03:12.700
It then can go on for sometime.

01:03:12.700 --> 01:03:17.130 position:56%
But once you have accomplished that,
then you are in a position to--

01:03:17.130 --> 01:03:21.030
in my sort of words, you have
gained your ticket of admission

01:03:21.030 --> 01:03:24.950
into that kind of larger
international society of states.

01:03:24.950 --> 01:03:27.420
And the reason why I kind of
brought this story of the emergence

01:03:27.420 --> 01:03:29.900
of the state in the
American context is largely

01:03:29.900 --> 01:03:32.380
because I think it
provides that momentum

01:03:32.380 --> 01:03:38.110 position:56%
for thinking how a very fortunate
nation has come in late 18th century

01:03:38.110 --> 01:03:42.230
by sometimes [inaudible]
circumstances to emerge

01:03:42.230 --> 01:03:46.030
as a global actor on
the international stage,

01:03:46.030 --> 01:03:47.920
an event which doesn't
really happen until--

01:03:47.920 --> 01:03:51.060
really until the late
19th, early 20th century.

01:03:51.060 --> 01:03:55.150 position:56%
But I do think you can already begin
to see how in late 18th century,

01:03:55.150 --> 01:04:01.140 position:56%
there is some manifestations of that
desire to emerge as an equal act

01:04:01.140 --> 01:04:05.100
or on the international stage.

01:04:05.100 --> 01:04:06.400
Yeah.

